# VideoRAG — Development Tasks

## Phase 0: Project Setup
- [ ] Create folder structure (`video-rag-app/`, `backend/`)
- [ ] Create `requirements.txt` with all dependencies
- [ ] Create `.gitignore` (ignore `temp_data/`, `chroma_db/`, `__pycache__/`)
- [ ] Create `backend/__init__.py`

## Phase 1: Backend — Audio Extraction & Transcription (`processor.py`)
- [ ] Implement `extract_audio(video_path) -> audio_path` using `ffmpeg-python`
- [ ] Implement `transcribe_audio(audio_path) -> list[segments]` using `faster-whisper` (base model, int8)
- [ ] Return segment dicts with `start`, `end`, `text` fields

## Phase 2: Backend — Chunking & Vector Store (`vector_store.py`)
- [ ] Implement Sliding Window chunking (60s window, 10s overlap) over raw segments
- [ ] Implement `add_video(video_id, segments)` — chunk, embed, store in ChromaDB
- [ ] Implement `search(query, top_k) -> results` — semantic search via cosine similarity
- [ ] Use `sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` for embeddings
- [ ] Use ChromaDB persistent local client (`chroma_db/` directory)

## Phase 3: Frontend — Streamlit UI (`app.py`)
- [ ] Inject custom CSS to override Streamlit defaults (padding, fonts, palette)
- [ ] Build hero search bar (centered, rounded, shadow)
- [ ] Build video upload widget + processing status/progress
- [ ] Build result cards (white, rounded, left-border accent, clickable)
- [ ] Wire result click → video player seek to timestamp
- [ ] Integrate video player with `st.video` and timestamp control

## Phase 4: Integration & Polish
- [ ] End-to-end flow: Upload → Process → Search → Seek
- [ ] Error handling and edge cases
- [ ] Manual verification with a sample video
